Hello everyone, thanks for using my app I hope it has been helpful. Believe it or not, RentBurrow was made by a non-CS solo developer (me) for the past year... I apologize if you have encountered any bugs or ugly UI/UX. Moreso, I am happy to announce that I have quit my job to work on this fulltime. Not just me, but 2 very talented friends of mine (Jimmy Zidan Guo & Vincent Chiang) have also quit their jobs and turned down offers from companies like Facebook. What we are working on is currently a secret, but we can say that it will make your life a whole lot easier. For now, please enjoy our growing library of 360' virtual tours (rentburrow.com/sage-5). We would also appreciate any suggestions or bug reports if you encounter them, just send me a fb message. Thanks for all your support Waterloo, see you soon!

=============

You can also compare 8/12 month leases to make sure you're getting the best deal. It makes finding housing A WHOLE LOT EASIER. Give it a try, I'm sure you will find it super useful!  :)

Review of kw4rent at 250 Lester st. PH01

I lived at this place for the past year and struggled to get help from kw4rent for their major ceiling leak problem.

When we were signing our contract we were shown a different unit with the same layout. This is usually fine, except when i walked in our unit, it had ceilings patched with pads (female hygiene product). I now assume that the previous tenant had the same problem and solved the problem with a temporary solution. Not knowing that there was a leaking problem, i removed all the pads from the ceiling. 

After that every time it rained, we had water leak in our bedrooms, kitchen, and the hallway. I've requested multiple help on the kw webpage, which had fast response but said technicians will come on a later date and that they can't really help. After multiple complains, they provided us with buckets to hold water. The maintenance manager once came and gave me his business card and told me to email him, but in the end he just told me it takes time to find source of the issue. In the beginning, i requested only for laundry compensations since the leak happened on my bed. Their promises on compensations were not followed up, and soon after the manager stopped replying to my "its leaking again" emails. 

I moved in mid September 2016, and the first leak report i handed in was October 16th 2016 (the pad was attached on the ceiling for a bit on the ceiling). The last leak in our unit, that I observed, happened July 2017. The third ticket on my maintenance request was marked complete August 5th 2017 (Third ticket because they always said it was complete and there was always leaks and I had to recreate tickets). 

Attached are some pictures of the leaked areas. I'm done with living with kw4rent and wanted to share my story to possible future kw4rent tenants.
